We can compute that
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{p} &= \operatorname{proj}_{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \frac{\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \frac{-1}{5} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \begin{pmatrix} -\frac{2}{5} \\ -\frac{1}{5} \end{pmatrix}.
\end{align*}Since $\mathbf{p}$ is the midpoint of $\mathbf{v}$ and $\mathbf{r},$ $\mathbf{p} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} + \mathbf{r}}{2},$ so
\[\mathbf{r} = 2 \mathbf{p} - \mathbf{v} = 2 \begin{pmatrix} -\frac{2}{5} \\ -\frac{1}{5} \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 6/5 \\ -17/5 \end{pmatrix}}.\]

We can write
\[f(x) = \sqrt{(x - 5)^2 + 3^2} - \sqrt{x^2 + 4}.\]Let $P = (x,0),$ $A = (5,3),$ and $B = (0,2).$  Then $f(x) = PA - PB.$

[asy]
